The people of Gbaramatu Kingdom, Warri South-West local government area of Delta State have decried the abandonment of the multi-billion dollar Export Processing Zone (EPZ) Gas Revolution Industrial Park, Ogidigben, and Deep Sea Port Project, Gbaramatu by the federal government. Chief Godspower Gbenekama (JP), in a statement he issued on behalf of Gbaramatu Traditional Council, said that the projects would have created thousands of direct and indirect jobs at a time the APC  government’s job creation statistics and figures were taking a beating for not living up to the promises made to Nigerians. While lamenting the neglect of the  federal government despite the kingdom’s huge contribution to the development of the country, he noted that the people of Gbaramatu had kept to their social contract that helped ended the previous dangerous era of agitation which was prevalent in Gbaramatu Kingdom. “We will state one of the few but inexhaustible list of grievances that threatened the continued peaceful upholding of this social contract that has now turned one-sided. The Omadinor-excravos road project that was started, and would have led to greater peaceful co-existence and dramatically improved economic relations between the neighbouring local governments, has been put on indefinite hold under this administration,” he said. 